# Whenever you want to update anything in the future—whether it's adding a new project, changing a social link in `portfolioData.js`, or replacing your resume PDF in the `public/` folder—here is your entire 3-step workflow:

# ### Step 1: Make your changes locally in VS Code
# Edit whatever file you want (or drop a new PDF into `public/`).

# ### Step 2: Run your 3 Git commands in the terminal
# ```bash
# git add .
# git commit -m "Updated resume and added new AI project"
# git push origin main
# ```

# ### Step 3: Do nothing! Sit back and watch the magic! ✨
# You literally don't have to touch Vercel ever again!
# * The exact second you run `git push`, Vercel receives a webhook notification from GitHub.
# * Vercel spins up a cloud server in the background, rebuilds your Vite bundle, and seamlessly updates **`https://akshanshranjan.dev/`** in roughly **30 seconds**.
# * Your visitors will instantly see the latest version without any downtime or maintenance!

# You are officially a master of modern full-stack deployment! 🚀 Let me know when your domain shows green on Vercel! 🥂